  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a randomized controlled trail. A total of 28 individuals with aMCI will be randomly
      assigned to either the ISE group or control group. The ISE intervention conducts three times
      a week for 16 weeks. Outcomes are measured at baseline and after intervention. The primary
      outcomes are the Chinese version verbal learning test (CVVLT), selective reminding test
      (SRT), and logic memory test (Wechsler Memory Scale). The secondary outcomes are Montreal
      Cognitive Assessment (MoCA) for cognitive function, and trail making test Part A &amp; B (TMT-A &amp;
      B), Stroop test, and 25-item Executive Interview (C-EXIT 25) for executive function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
